job_description:
Job description
• Lead the development and management of effective B2B business strategies to achieve the group's growth goals.
• Develop and maintain key business relationships with partners and customers.
• Build and deploy B2B business, expand markets, focusing on corporate customers.
• Search, establish and develop relationships with strategic partners and large customers (businesses, corporations).
• Leading and optimizing sales team performance, driving revenue and sustainable growth.
• Coordinate with internal departments (Marketing, Product, Finance) to build solutions suitable to business customer needs.
• Research the market, propose growth options and effective business models.




Job requirements

• University degree in Economics, Finance, Business Administration or related fields.
• Have at least 10 years of experience in the field of B2B business, including at least 5 years of business management at large-scale enterprises or corporate models. Priority is given to candidates with experience in the Information Technology, Communications and Security industry. (Head of Department, Deputy Director of Sales or equivalent).
• Have extensive relationships with C-level levels, ability to find, develop and maintain relationships with partners and customers.
• Ability to lead, guide, train and optimize sales team performance.
• Dynamic, creative and passionate about business..
• Good communication and teamwork skills.
• Ability to inspire, lead, motivate and coach teams




BENEFITS


• Attractive salary, negotiable based on capacity + Business Performance Bonus + ESOP Bonus for Management level;
• High-end health insurance for Managers;
• Annual salary review policy;
• Bonus regime: Bonus on all holidays and New Year; Year-end bonus based on company's business results;
• Working with many experts in many fields, high opportunities for personal development;
• Enjoy full insurance benefits and days off and holidays according to company regulations and current laws;
• Enjoy welfare benefits and collective cultural activities: Team Building, year-end Gala, birthdays, holidays...;
• Work in a friendly, dynamic, professional environment;
• There are high opportunities for advancement and development.

